This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation classification. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes and compares different neural architectures for the task. Additionally, it could be categorized under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural networks for a specific task. "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as it deals with neural network models. Finally, "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) could be a relevant category as relation classification is a common task in information retrieval.
